Package cosc201.utilities

Class Timer

java.lang.Object
cosc201.utilities.Timer
public class Timer extends Object
A simple wall-clock timer designed for collecting data on experiments in COSC201

  • Constructor Details

    • Timer

      public Timer()
      Constructs a timer (no initialisation required)

  • Method Details

    • start

      public void start()
      Start the timer. Note that this throws a runtime exception if the timer is already running.

    • stop

      public long stop()
      Stop the timer. The time taken is returned and also added to the internal list of times. Note that this throws a runtime exception if the timer is not running.
      Returns:
      The time taken (in nanoseconds) since the last start().

    • getTime

      public long getTime()
      Return the time taken for the last run of this timer.
      Returns:
      Time (in nanoseconds) for the last run of this timer.

    • getTimes

      public List<Long> getTimes()
      Return the times recorded for all runs of this timer.
      Returns:
      A list view of the times recorded by this timer.

    • getTotalTime

      public long getTotalTime()
      Compute and return the total time recorded for all runs of this timer.
      Returns:
      The total time recorded by this time (in nanoseconds).

    • reset

      public void reset()
      Reset the timer. That is, stop it and clear the list of times recorded.

    • getTimeInMs

      public long getTimeInMs()
      Return the time taken for the last run of this timer in milliseconds.
      Returns:
      Time (in milliseconds) for the last run of this timer.
